Class overview

Constants and helpers for operating on people.

This is the URI you will use for accessing information about people. Every CSS/person which is accessible from SocialProvider has an entry in this table. You can search for people using GLOBAL_ID, name etc. You can find information about both of the following:
  • People you have a relationship to.
  • People you don't have a relationship to.
Of course for people to whom you have a relationship (e.g. friends) might be represented with more information than those you do not have a relationship to. But the method of accessing this information is the same for all people.

Insert

Applications cannot insert people.

Insert will be supported for SyncAdapters only. SyncAdapters have to set the following parameters in the query in order to insert successfully:
  • GLOBAL_ID
  • NAME
  • DESCRIPTION (Optional)
  • EMAIL (Optional)
  • ORIGIN
  • CREATION_DATE
  • SYNC_STATUS
The following parameters can also be set:

Update

Applications can update:
  • NAME
  • EMAIL
  • DESCRIPTION
SyncAdapters can update:
  • NAME
  • DESCRIPTION
  • EMAIL
  • ORIGIN
  • CREATION_DATE
  • SYNC_STATUS

Delete

Applications cannot delete people.

SyncAdapters can delete people by either appending _ID to the end of the query URI or using a standard selection.

Query

Applications can query for people using standard query URI or using _ID as the last part of the URI.
